---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Jevan Cousins"
  description="Jevan Cousins is an applied AI engineer based in London, UK. Solution Architect at Allianz Global Investors with expertise in AI, data engineering, and full-stack product development."
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="font-display font-bold mb-8">About</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6">
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-primary">
        I am an applied AI engineer based in London, UK, currently finishing up as Solution Architect at Allianz Global Investors. Over four years, I have architected enterprise AI systems, built production data pipelines serving 176 billion euros in Fixed Income assets, and engineered the infrastructure for AI adoption across global teams.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-primary">
        I am most energised by problems at the intersection of AI and product: taking abstract research findings and shipping them as systems that users rely on. At AllianzGI, I designed the firm's first enterprise agentic AI system for investment services support, orchestrating five system integrations to reach user testing within a tight deadline. I led the technical rollout of MSCI BarraOne for performance attribution, completing a programme that had failed twice over seven years. I pioneered AI adoption across operations by identifying 50+ use cases and building proof-of-concept applications.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-primary">
        In parallel, I am building two products from scratch. Lineup is a concert discovery iOS app paired with a production data platform ingesting 1 million+ events from six APIs via Apache Airflow, transforming them through dbt, and landing them in BigQuery. NutriPlan is an AI meal planning app with a FastAPI backend using GPT-4o and vector embeddings to generate personalised weekly meal plans. JobHunter is a job search automation platform using Claude API for intelligent job scoring and Playwright for scraping.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-primary">
        My background is in physics and mathematics from UCL. I hold a 2:1 BSc Natural Sciences with a dissertation on deep learning for image reconstruction, and I've completed certifications in data science, SQL, and AI from DataCamp.
      </p>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-primary">
        I am currently job-searching for applied AI roles in Paris or London, ideally combining system architecture with product shipped to real users. I am curious about founder-path opportunities as well.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
